# API consumption (Marham frontend)

HTTP APIs live in **this Next.js app** at `app/api/` (TypeORM + MySQL). The frontend calls them via `lib/services/*` using `NEXT_PUBLIC_MARHAM_API_URL` (defaults to `http://localhost:3001`).

## Adding a new endpoint

1. Add Route Handler in `app/api/` (`export const runtime = "nodejs"`)
2. Add service/repository logic in `lib/server/`
3. Add path to `lib/constants/marham-api-endpoints.ts`
4. Add typed fetch helper in `lib/services/`

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — lib helper calling local API (server or client)
import { fetchDoctorsListing } from "@/lib/services/doctors-listing-service"

// Server Component
const { doctors, meta } = await fetchDoctorsListing({ page: 1 }, { revalidate: 60 })

// Client Component
const { doctors, meta } = await fetchDoctorsListing({ page: currentPage + 1 })
```

## Env

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_MARHAM_API_URL` — API base URL (e.g. `http://localhost:3001`)
- `DB_*`, `MARHAM_URL`, CDN vars — server-only in `.env` (never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` for secrets)

## Legacy

`MarhamOne/` (NestJS on :3000) is reference only; do not add new endpoints there for this frontend.
